==English==

===Etymology===
Adaptation from Old French ''gingembras, gingimbrat'' meaning preserved ginger which was an adaptation of medieval Latin ''*gingi(m)brāt-um'', (ginger which perhaps had a pharmaceutical use for some medicinal preparation), formed from medieval Latin ''gingiber'', [[ginger]]. The 3rd syllable was early confounded with ''bread'', and the insertion of an r in the 2nd syllable completed the semblance of a compound word.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=|[[ginger]][[bread]]|-}}

# A sweet [[biscuit]] or [[cookie]] whose main [[flavouring]] is [[ginger]].
# {{US}} A spice cake mainly flavored with ginger; rarely frosted, but usually dusted with [[powdered sugar]].
# {{architecture}} The [[flamboyant]] applied [[ornament]] associated with [[Victorian]]-era buildings. 

